    <Fortune>Buyback shops pay nicely once \nyou learn to negotiate.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>I see you playing flip-flop \nand winning a fortune!</Fortune>
    <Fortune>The lender will give \nyou money at good rates.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Healers can help you \nafter you find the Juton bush.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Carry gold - merchants might \nsell you museum coins.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Carry climbing gear. \nIt will prove handy.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>The path to greatness lies \nthrough the museum.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>The warlord's agents \nare everywhere.  Watch out!</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Learn to lie - so you'll \nmaster the Stones of Wisdom.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>The pirate's cave is \nwest of Eagle Hollow.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Only the 4 jewels can \nthwart the evil compendium.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>You need herbs to \nsucceed in dungeons.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>It works best to club the \nslash nettle to death.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Keep money in the \nbank in case of death.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Castle doors require \nfour different keys.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Behind the castle gardens \nlies a special flower.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>In the right places, magic \nseeds make you invisible.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Hidden passageways line the castle! \nLook carefully!!!</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Many guards protect the mints. \nIt's worth the fight.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>An evil warlord's man \nwas here asking about you.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>The winged horse can \nfly across the sea.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Healers are more than they seem. \nBide your time.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>The Maston Leaper fears \nonly a bladed staff.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>You must master the spiral room.\n    </Fortune>
    <Fortune>Use the bladed staff to \nneutralize the Neural Cloud.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Go back to school. \nYou can learn more.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Speak to the temptress \nin the castle.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>The castle wizards know many answers.\n</Fortune>
    <Fortune>There's a path around \nthe castle gas trap.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>You can't climb up the \nknight's dungeon.  Stay away!</Fortune>
    <Fortune>You can flail the \nsea swallow to death.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Watch out.  The agents \nmay be after you.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>One day you will travel \nhigh above the sea.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Talk to the guardians of the scroll.\n</Fortune>
    <Fortune>Learn the password to the \ncastle wizard's quarters.</Fortune>
    <Fortune>You can trust the winged horse.\n</Fortune>
